It bundles the following third-party components:

- Mermaid (https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid) — MIT License.
  A minified runtime is embedded as internal/assets/mermaid.min.js.gz and
  inlined into generated HTML diagram previews. Mermaid is distributed under
  the MIT License: https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid/blob/develop/LICENSE

- AWS Architecture Icons (https://aws.amazon.com/architecture/icons/) —
  used for visualization in accordance with AWS's icon terms (attribution
  required). A curated subset of SVGs is embedded under
  internal/assets/aws-icons/.

- HCL (https://github.com/hashicorp/hcl) — Mozilla Public License 2.0.
  Linked as the Go module github.com/hashicorp/hcl/v2 to parse Terraform
  HCL source in internal/audit/parsers/. HCL is distributed under the
  MPL-2.0: https://github.com/hashicorp/hcl/blob/main/LICENSE

- go-cty (https://github.com/zclconf/go-cty) — MIT License.
  Linked as the Go module github.com/zclconf/go-cty (HCL's value/type
  system, used alongside it in internal/audit/parsers/). go-cty is
  distributed under the MIT License:
  https://github.com/zclconf/go-cty/blob/main/LICENSE

Go module dependencies are listed in go.mod / go.sum. Their licenses
(Apache-2.0, MIT, BSD, MPL-2.0) are permissive and compatible with
Apache-2.0 distribution.
